Wash and dry all produce. Heat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Remove husks from @tomatillos{8%ounce}, then halve. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and arrange cut-sides down. Add @corn on the cob{2} to sheet. Season both with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Broil or bake until soft, ~{8-10%minutes}. Remove from sheet and let cool. Set oven to 400 degrees.

Meanwhile, take out @butter{2%tablespoon} and let sit at room temperature to soften. Zest @lime{1} until you have 1 tsp, then cut into halves. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1} until you have 2 TBSP. Mince @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat.

Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Rub @chicken breasts{12%ounce} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, half the garlic, half the zest, @honey{1%tsp} (we sent more), and a pinch of salt and pepper. Add to pan and sear until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per side. Place on a baking sheet. (TIP: Use sheet used for tomatillos.) Roast until no longer pink in center, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Place tomatillos in a #medium bowl{} and mash with a #fork{} (they should still be slightly chunky). Halve, pit, and peel @avocado{1}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Add to bowl with tomatillos along with remaining zest, remaining garlic, shallot, half the jalapeño, lime juice, and @sugar{1%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

In a #small bowl{}, mix butter, remaining @honey{1%tsp}, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

Let chicken rest ~{5%minutes} after removing from oven, then thinly slice. Rub corn with honey butter. Divide corn and chicken between plates. Spoon salsa over chicken and serve.

> Tomatillos like to hide their charms. First, there's the outer husks, which have to be peeled away in order to reveal the fruit. And even once you get to that fruit, it still looks a bit funny, like a green tomato gone awry. But once you cook tomatillos, they release all of their delicious, succulent juices, which mingle with creamy avocado, garlic-rubbed chicken, and sweet buttered corn in this recipe.